<dl id="n53097d"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n53" href="#n53097d">N53 (VI.B.46)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n53all.htm#n53097d"> 97(d)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Mills, <small>Red</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n53097d"><li>FW 341.03 </li><li><a href="../../flex/md/lexmd.htm#n53097d">2010</a> </li><li><a href="../../flex/md/l39md.htm#n53097d">1939</a> </li><li><ms href="#n53097d">MS BL 47480-75v</ms> </li><li>JJA 55:142 <a name="mdd5" href="../../FF/fdra/mda.htm#mdd5">Usage</a> </li><li> <a href="../../flex/md/mdd5.htm#n53097d">Draft: II.3&sect;4.5</a></li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources">Suddenly the saphead seemed to swarm with men who leaped into it out of the silent mists; a bullet-headed man seized John by the collar and yanked him out; the rest of the party seized the <mark>Mills</mark> bombs lying at the saphead, threw them at the sleeping picket near the fire-trench, and followed John&apos;s captor. <small> H.C. McNeile (&ldquo;Sapper&rdquo;) <a name="SJW" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#SJW"><cite title="source">John Walters</cite></a> (1927) The Awakening of John Walters, 13</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: [Army slang] Mills: the Mills bomb, serrated like a pine-apple. On exploding, it fragmented into shrapnel &mdash; lethal chucks of metal named after General Henry Shrapnel who first conceived of the device of loading the body of a shell with small pellets, to be expelled with horrific effect on impact. </mm> </dd></dl>
